The paper deals with the problem of storing versioned data in distributed storage systems, which is a topic related to data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The proposed technique involves compressed sensing (cs.IT) and erasure coding (cs.CR), which are both relevant subfields. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of delta encoding techniques (cs.DC) and compares the proposed method to a baseline system that incorporates concepts from Rsync, a delta encoding technique.
